President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 11, 2011, as National Grandparents Day in the United States. In the proclamation, he highlights the important role that grandparents play in families and communities, as well as their contributions to the nation. He emphasizes the need to support and provide for grandparents, particularly through programs like Social Security and Medicare. President Obama also calls upon all Americans to honor their own grandparents and those in their community.